verses.text_plain: Bow down thine ear, O Lord, hear me: for I am poor and needy.
verses.verse_html:
1Bow down thine ear, O Lord, hear me: for I am poor and needy. ▼
▼ A Prayer…: or, A Prayer, being a Psalm of David

footnotes.body_text: ▼ A Prayer…: or, A Prayer, being a Psalm of David
footnotes.body_html: ▼ A Prayer…: or, A Prayer, being a Psalm of David

verses.text_plain: Preserve my soul; for I am holy: O thou my God, save thy servant that trusteth in thee.
verses.verse_html:
2Preserve my soul; for I am holy: O thou my God, save thy servant that trusteth in thee. ▼
▼ holy: or, one whom thou favourest

footnotes.body_text: ▼ holy: or, one whom thou favourest
footnotes.body_html: ▼ holy: or, one whom thou favourest

verses.text_plain: Be merciful unto me, O Lord: for I cry unto thee daily.
verses.verse_html:
3Be merciful unto me, O Lord: for I cry unto thee daily. ▼
▼ daily: or, all the day

footnotes.body_html: ▼ daily: or, all the day

verses.text_plain: Rejoice the soul of thy servant: for unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.
verses.verse_html: 4Rejoice the soul of thy servant: for unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.

verses.text_plain: For thou, Lord, art good, and ready to forgive; and plenteous in mercy unto all them that call upon thee.
verses.verse_html: 5For thou, Lord, art good, and ready to forgive; and plenteous in mercy unto all them that call upon thee.

verses.text_plain: Give ear, O Lord, unto my prayer; and attend to the voice of my supplications.
verses.verse_html: 6Give ear, O Lord, unto my prayer; and attend to the voice of my supplications.

verses.text_plain: In the day of my trouble I will call upon thee: for thou wilt answer me.
verses.verse_html: 7In the day of my trouble I will call upon thee: for thou wilt answer me.

tokens.text: upon thee: for thou wilt answer

verses.text_plain: Among the gods there is none like unto thee, O Lord; neither are there any works like unto thy works.
verses.verse_html: 8Among the gods there is none like unto thee, O Lord; neither are there any works like unto thy works.

tokens.text: none like unto thee, O Lord

verses.text_plain: All nations whom thou hast made shall come and worship before thee, O Lord; and shall glorify thy name.
verses.verse_html: 9All nations whom thou hast made shall come and worship before thee, O Lord; and shall glorify thy name.

verses.text_plain: For thou art great, and doest wondrous things: thou art God alone.
verses.verse_html: 10For thou art great, and doest wondrous things: thou art God alone.

verses.text_plain: Teach me thy way, O Lord; I will walk in thy truth: unite my heart to fear thy name.
verses.verse_html: 11Teach me thy way, O Lord; I will walk in thy truth: unite my heart to fear thy name.

verses.text_plain: I will praise thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart: and I will glorify thy name for evermore.
verses.verse_html: 12I will praise thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart: and I will glorify thy name for evermore.

verses.text_plain: For great is thy mercy toward me: and thou hast delivered my soul from the lowest hell.
verses.verse_html:
13For great is thy mercy toward me: and thou hast delivered my soul from the lowest hell. ▼
▼ hell: or, grave

tokens.text: toward me: and thou hast delivered

verses.text_plain: O God, the proud are risen against me, and the assemblies of violent men have sought after my soul; and have not set thee before them.
verses.verse_html:
14O God, the proud are risen against me, and the assemblies of violent men have sought after my soul; and have not set thee before them. ▼
▼ violent: Heb. terrible

verses.text_plain: But thou, O Lord, art a God full of compassion, and gracious, longsuffering, and plenteous in mercy and truth.
verses.verse_html: 15But thou, O Lord, art a God full of compassion, and gracious, longsuffering, and plenteous in mercy and truth.

verses.text_plain: O turn unto me, and have mercy upon me; give thy strength unto thy servant, and save the son of thine handmaid.
verses.verse_html: 16O turn unto me, and have mercy upon me; give thy strength unto thy servant, and save the son of thine handmaid.

verses.text_plain: Shew me a token for good; that they which hate me may see it, and be ashamed: because thou, Lord, hast holpen me, and comforted me.
verses.verse_html: 17Shew me a token for good; that they which hate me may see it, and be ashamed: because thou, Lord, hast holpen me, and comforted me.
